      },
      "source": [
        "## .csv file is the cleaned up to extract desired Features for the deep learning step to get maximum efficiency"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "SmK8OaAbhdzP",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "outputId": "5273cc32-a75c-45ff-984d-0f3a48b4055d",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 399
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "meta_train_normal=metadata[(metadata[\"Label\"]==\"Normal\")&(metadata[\"Dataset_type\"]==\"TRAIN\")]\n",
        "meta_train_pnemonia=metadata[(metadata[\"Label\"]==\"Pnemonia\")&(metadata[\"Dataset_type\"]==\"TRAIN\")&(metadata[\"Label_1_Virus_category\"]==\"Virus\")&(metadata[\"Label_2_Virus_category\"].isnull())]\n",
        "meta_train_covid=metadata[(metadata[\"Label\"]==\"Pnemonia\")&(metadata[\"Dataset_type\"]==\"TRAIN\")&(metadata[\"Label_2_Virus_category\"]==\"COVID-19\")&(metadata[\"Label_1_Virus_category\"]==\"Virus\")]\n",
        "\n",
        "meta_test_normal=metadata[(metadata[\"Label\"]==\"Normal\")&(metadata[\"Dataset_type\"]==\"TEST\")]\n",
        "meta_test_pnemonia=metadata[(metadata[\"Label\"]==\"Pnemonia\")&(metadata[\"Dataset_type\"]==\"TEST\")&(metadata[\"Label_1_Virus_category\"]==\"Virus\")&(metadata[\"Label_2_Virus_category\"].isnull())]\n",
        "meta_test_covid=metadata[(metadata[\"Label\"]==\"Pnemonia\")&(metadata[\"Dataset_type\"]==\"TEST\")&(metadata[\"Label_2_Virus_category\"]==\"COVID-19\")&(metadata[\"Label_1_Virus_category\"]==\"Virus\")]\n",
        "#meta_train_normal.count()\n",
        "#meta_train_pnemonia.count()\n",
        "#meta_train_covid.count()\n",
        "#meta_train_pnemonia.head()\n",
        "#meta_test_covid.count()\n",
        "meta_train_normal=meta_train_normal.assign(Class=meta_train_normal[\"Label\"])\n",
        "meta_train_pnemonia=meta_train_pnemonia.assign(Class=meta_train_pnemonia[\"Label\"])\n",
        "meta_train_covid=meta_train_covid.assign(Class=meta_train_covid[\"Label_2_Virus_category\"])\n",
        "meta_train=pd.concat([meta_train_normal,meta_train_pnemonia,meta_train_covid])\n",
        "meta_train=meta_train[[\"X_ray_image_name\",\"Class\"]]\n",
        "meta_train\n",
        "meta_test_normal=meta_test_normal.assign(Class=meta_test_normal[\"Label\"])\n",
        "meta_test_pnemonia=meta_test_pnemonia.assign(Class=meta_test_pnemonia[\"Label\"])\n",
        "meta_test_covid=meta_test_covid.assign(Class=meta_test_covid[\"Label_2_Virus_category\"])\n",
        "meta_test=pd.concat([meta_test_normal,meta_test_pnemonia,meta_test_covid])\n",
        "meta_test=meta_test[[\"X_ray_image_name\",\"Class\"]]\n",
        "meta_test"
      ],

      "cell_type": "markdown",

      },
      "source": [
        "### Use ImageDataGenerator from keras as it is very helpful for preprocessing the image data for spliting into batches and make varients of them"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "EzLhxKftfXv9",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {}
      },
      "source": [
        "from keras_preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator"
      ],
      "execution_count": 0,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "hJPgz632UaQ2",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {}
      },
      "source": [
        "train=pd.read_csv(\"train.csv\",dtype=str)\n",
        "test=pd.read_csv(\"test.csv\",dtype=str)"
      ],
      "execution_count": 0,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Z9lXSpbYJpwJ",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Now rescale the image cause we know pixel values are from 0 to 255"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3m7mHJj1V2Q1",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {}
      },
      "source": [
        "datagen = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1. / 255,\n",
        "                                   rotation_range=40,\n",
        "                                   width_shift_range=0.2,\n",
        "                                   height_shift_range=0.2,\n",
        "                                   shear_range=0.2,\n",
        "                                   zoom_range=0.2,\n",
        "                                   horizontal_flip=True,\n",
        "                                   fill_mode='nearest',validation_split=0.25)"
      ],
      "execution_count": 0,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "cNzvOvgy9s_W",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {}
      },
      "source": [
        "batch_size = 20\n",
        "epochs = 15\n",
        "IMG_HEIGHT = 150\n",
        "IMG_WIDTH = 150"
      ],
      "execution_count": 0,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "oHdkwBNzJ9mf",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "Use the flow_from_dataframe() method from ImageDataGenerator doc can be found here [flow_from_dataframe()](https://keras.io/api/preprocessing/image/)\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "jzckf41vMDVX",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "```\n",
        "ImageDataGenerator.flow_from_dataframe(\n",
        "    dataframe,\n",
        "    directory=None,\n",
        "    x_col=\"filename\",\n",
        "    y_col=\"class\",\n",
        "    weight_col=None,\n",
        "    target_size=(256, 256),\n",
        "    color_mode=\"rgb\",\n",
        "    classes=None,\n",
        "    class_mode=\"categorical\",\n",
        "    batch_size=32,\n",
        "    shuffle=True,\n",
        "    seed=None,\n",
        "    save_to_dir=None,\n",
        "    save_prefix=\"\",\n",
        "    save_format=\"png\",\n",
        "    subset=None,\n",
        "    interpolation=\"nearest\",\n",
        "    validate_filenames=True,\n",
        "    **kwargs\n",
        ")\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "C4sx64P8V3I7",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "outputId": "334277f9-a5bd-41b3-9cc0-43081f72ce1f",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 52
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "train_generator=datagen.flow_from_dataframe(\n",
        "dataframe=train,\n",
        "directory=\"Coronahack-Chest-XRay-Dataset/Coronahack-Chest-XRay-Dataset/train/\",\n",
        "x_col=\"X_ray_image_name\",\n",
        "y_col=\"Class\",\n",
        "subset=\"training\",\n",
        "batch_size=batch_size,\n",
        "shuffle=True,\n",
        "seed=32,\n",
        "target_size=(IMG_HEIGHT, IMG_WIDTH),\n",
        "class_mode=\"categorical\")\n",
        "\n",
        "valid_generator=datagen.flow_from_dataframe(\n",
        "dataframe=train,\n",
        "directory=\"Coronahack-Chest-XRay-Dataset/Coronahack-Chest-XRay-Dataset/train/\",\n",
        "x_col=\"X_ray_image_name\",\n",
        "y_col=\"Class\",\n",
        "subset=\"validation\",\n",
        "shuffle=True,\n",
        "seed=32,\n",
        "target_size=(IMG_HEIGHT,IMG_WIDTH),\n",
        "class_mode=\"categorical\")"

      "source": [

        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {}
      },
      "source": [
        "from tensorflow.keras import datasets, layers, models\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n"

      "execution_count": 0,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kay1MxFD_2rZ",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {}
      },
      "source": [
        "sample_training_images, _ = next(train_generator)"
      ],
      "execution_count": 0,
      "outputs": []

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "shyTYFcZMtg-",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "## We plot the sample images using matplotlib"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "AEwtD8xQALZk",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "outputId": "be226f56-d22a-43b5-894d-6e7fc193946e",

          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",

      },
      "source": [
        "def plotImages(images_arr):\n",
        "    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 5, figsize=(20,20))\n",
        "    axes = axes.flatten()\n",
        "    for img, ax in zip( images_arr, axes):\n",
        "        ax.imshow(img)\n",
        "        ax.axis('off')\n",
        "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "    \n",
        "plotImages(sample_training_images[:5])"

        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {}
      },
      "source": [
        "STEP_SIZE_TRAIN=train_generator.n//train_generator.batch_size\n",
        "STEP_SIZE_VALID=valid_generator.n//valid_generator.batch_size\n",
        "STEP_SIZE_TEST=test_generator.n//test_generator.batch_size"
      ],
      "execution_count": 0,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "tKszK7pvM2ku",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "The Model is now created as below"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "q5tWVQUBX3tC",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {}
      },
      "source": [
        "model = models.Sequential()\n",
        "model.add(layers.Conv2D(32, (3, 3), activation='relu', input_shape=(IMG_HEIGHT, IMG_WIDTH, 3),padding=\"valid\"))\n",
        "model.add(layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)))\n",
        "model.add(layers.Conv2D(32, (3, 3), activation='relu',padding=\"valid\"))\n",
        "model.add(layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)))\n",
        "model.add(layers.Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu',padding=\"valid\"))\n",
        "model.add(layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)))\n",
        "model.add(layers.Flatten())\n",
        "model.add(layers.Dense(256,activation=\"relu\"))\n",
        "model.add(layers.Dropout(0.3))\n",
        "model.add(layers.Dense(3,activation='softmax'))"
      ],
      "execution_count": 0,
      "outputs": []
    },

      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
